            "answer_text": "Impressed, yes. It was unexpected, Cortes was send on a mission of diplomacy and exploration, not conquest. The governor of Cuba, Diego Velazquez was sent to stop Cortes after finding out his real intentions.  Here we have Diego telling Hernan \u201cPlease dont, we want to make friends, not enemies! Plus you dont have permission from the crown\u201d Many favored it and many others did not but you have to look at it in the point of view of the era. The Ottomans gave a huge blow to Christendom when they conquered Constantinople, so here where the Spanish saying \u201cOh yeah, you conquered Constantinople, Egypt and Hungary? Well guess what?! We conquered THREE great unknown civilizations and one of them had the biggest city of the WORLD!\u201d  Here we have the world in the year 1600, Spain and the Ottomans where the biggest and most powerful powers in Europe at the time. When I was a kid I wondered if Tenochtitlan was truly the biggest city of the world or just a lying attempt by the Spanish to brag to the Muslims and Europe but historians do find it among the top 10 and quite possibly bigger than any European city of its time.  ",
